"{\"uid\": \"thestar.com.my-tech-tech-news-2024-08-02-googles-olympics-ad-was-designed-to-be-uplifting-instead-many-are-finding-it-dystopian\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Friday, 02 Aug 2024  Alphabet CEO Sundar Pichai.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 48, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 34, \"end\": 47, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sundar_Pichai\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Sundar Pichai\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sundar_Pichai\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sundar_Pichai\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"On social media, Google's ad drew backlash from some worried about AI's role in such an emotional and personal task as writing a fan letter.\", \"from\": 49, \"to\": 189, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 66, \"end\": 72, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 2.338298194017821e-13, \"text\": \"Google\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google\"}, {\"begin\": 116, \"end\": 118, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.297431367532762e-14, \"text\": \"AI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"- The New York Times  Google's Olympics-themed advertisement for its generative AI chatbot Gemini has some debating what role artificial intelligence should play in our everyday lives.\", \"from\": 190, \"to\": 374, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 192, \"end\": 210, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_New_York_Times\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.176853356711436e-15, \"text\": \"The New York Times\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_New_York_Times\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_New_York_Times\"}, {\"begin\": 212, \"end\": 218, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 2.338298194017821e-13, \"text\": \"Google\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google\"}, {\"begin\": 270, \"end\": 272, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.297431367532762e-14, \"text\": \"AI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The advertisement, titled \\\"Dear Sydney,\\\" features a dad helping his daughter use Gemini to produce an AI-crafted letter to the daughter's hero, Olympic hurdler Sydney McLaughlin-Levrone.\", \"from\": 376, \"to\": 562, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 457, \"end\": 463, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gemini_Awards\", \"score\": 0.9931073939191706, \"rank\": 0.0069404438263037565, \"text\": \"Gemini\", \"types\": [\"Q618779\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gemini_Awards\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gemini_Awards\"}, {\"begin\": 536, \"end\": 542, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\", \"score\": 0.9999955231005684, \"rank\": 4.440768013468917e-06, \"text\": \"Sydney\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In the ad, the father asks Gemini to help create a letter \\\"telling Sydney how inspiring she is, and be sure to mention that my daughter plans on breaking her world record one day.\", \"from\": 564, \"to\": 743, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 591, \"end\": 597, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gemini_Awards\", \"score\": 0.9931073939191706, \"rank\": 0.0069404438263037565, \"text\": \"Gemini\", \"types\": [\"Q618779\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gemini_Awards\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gemini_Awards\"}, {\"begin\": 631, \"end\": 637, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\", \"score\": 0.9999955231005684, \"rank\": 4.440768013468917e-06, \"text\": \"Sydney\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"(She says sorry, not sorry.)\\\"\", \"from\": 744, \"to\": 773, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"On social media, the ad drew backlash from some worried about AI's role in such an emotional and personal task as writing a fan letter.\", \"from\": 775, \"to\": 910, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 837, \"end\": 839, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.297431367532762e-14, \"text\": \"AI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Several called the message \\\"tone deaf\\\" and accused it of promoting laziness to create a letter devoid of meaning.\", \"from\": 911, \"to\": 1024, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Having a child use Gemini to write a one-time letter, that is supposed to be thoughtful, where spelling and grammar mistakes would have surely been forgiven, is just plain dumb.\", \"from\": 1026, \"to\": 1204, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1046, \"end\": 1052, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gemini_Awards\", \"score\": 0.9931073939191706, \"rank\": 0.0069404438263037565, \"text\": \"Gemini\", \"types\": [\"Q618779\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gemini_Awards\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gemini_Awards\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I find myself judging the dad hard lol,\\\" one user wrote on the subreddit r/CommercialsIHate.\", \"from\": 1205, \"to\": 1297, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Others online said the advertisement, like others promoting Gemini, signalled that tech companies want people to think less and off-load creative thinking or social interactions to machines.\", \"from\": 1299, \"to\": 1489, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"One such example criticised on Reddit included a Gemini commercial from May that, among other examples, showed a girl asking the chatbot what to say to her friends while they were sitting in front of her.\", \"from\": 1490, \"to\": 1694, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1521, \"end\": 1527, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reddit\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Reddit\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reddit\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reddit\"}, {\"begin\": 1539, \"end\": 1545, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gemini_Awards\", \"score\": 0.9931073939191706, \"rank\": 0.0069404438263037565, \"text\": \"Gemini\", \"types\": [\"Q618779\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gemini_Awards\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gemini_Awards\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Shelly Palmer, a media professor at Syracuse University, wrote in a blog post that the father in the ad was acting irresponsibly.\", \"from\": 1696, \"to\": 1825, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1696, \"end\": 1709, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shelly_Palmer\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Shelly Palmer\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shelly_Palmer\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shelly_Palmer\"}, {\"begin\": 1732, \"end\": 1751, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Syracuse_University\", \"score\": 0.9999992641535734, \"rank\": 3.21038654669433e-07, \"text\": \"Syracuse University\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q3918\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q2385804\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Syracuse_University\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Syracuse_University\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The father in the video is not encouraging his daughter to learn to express herself.\", \"from\": 1827, \"to\": 1912, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Instead of guiding her to use her own words and communicate authentically, he is teaching her to rely on AI for this critical human skill,\\\" Palmer wrote.\", \"from\": 1913, \"to\": 2066, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2018, \"end\": 2020, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.297431367532762e-14, \"text\": \"AI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In response to a request for comment, a Google spokesperson said the ad was meant to show how Gemini can provide a starting point or draft to help with the writing process.\", \"from\": 2068, \"to\": 2240, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2108, \"end\": 2114, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 2.338298194017821e-13, \"text\": \"Google\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google\"}, {\"begin\": 2162, \"end\": 2168, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gemini_Awards\", \"score\": 0.9931073939191706, \"rank\": 0.0069404438263037565, \"text\": \"Gemini\", \"types\": [\"Q618779\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gemini_Awards\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gemini_Awards\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We believe that AI can be a great tool for enhancing human creativity, but can never replace it,\\\" the spokesperson said.\", \"from\": 2242, \"to\": 2363, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2259, \"end\": 2261, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.297431367532762e-14, \"text\": \"AI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Despite the online criticism, the \\\"Dear Sydney\\\" commercial is one of the better performing Olympic advertisements, according to data from ad testing firm System1, cited byBusiness Insider.\", \"from\": 2365, \"to\": 2553, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The firm gave the ad a 4.4 out of 5.9 (a score it described as \\\"strong\\\") on its scale of how much the commercial could create long-term growth for the brand.\", \"from\": 2554, \"to\": 2711, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The ad had more than 300,000 views on YouTube as of Thursday.\", \"from\": 2712, \"to\": 2773, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2750, \"end\": 2757, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/YouTube\", \"score\": 0.9999999963997652, \"rank\": 3.600293494260244e-09, \"text\": \"YouTube\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/YouTube\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/YouTube\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It follows a coherent story, focuses on characters with agency and vitality, and prioritises people over the product,\\\" System1 chief customer officer Jon Evans toldBI.\", \"from\": 2775, \"to\": 2943, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2926, \"end\": 2935, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jon_Evans\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jon Evans\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jon_Evans\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jon_Evans\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Additionally, it champions diversity and inclusion by highlighting women in sports, providing young girls with role models.\\\"\", \"from\": 2944, \"to\": 3069, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"-Fortune.com/The New York Times  Thank you for your report!\", \"from\": 3070, \"to\": 3129, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3083, \"end\": 3101, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_New_York_Times\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.176853356711436e-15, \"text\": \"The New York Times\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_New_York_Times\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_New_York_Times\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Copyright \\u00a9 1995-Star Media Group Berhad [197101000523 (10894-D)]  Best viewed on Chrome browsers.\", \"from\": 3131, \"to\": 3229, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3213, \"end\": 3219, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google_Chrome\", \"score\": 0.9999852502529423, \"rank\": 1.4749964784786989e-05, \"text\": \"Chrome\", \"types\": [\"Q7397\", \"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google_Chrome\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google_Chrome\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"We would love to keep you posted on the latest promotion.\", \"from\": 3233, \"to\": 3290, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Kindly fill the form below  We hope you enjoy this feature!\", \"from\": 3291, \"to\": 3350, \"entities\": []}]}"